 {"id":"bd-17dh","title":"Create Icons utility with Unicode and ASCII fallbacks","description":"# Create Icons utility with Unicode and ASCII fallbacks

## Task Description

Create rch-common/src/ui/icons.rs with an Icons utility that provides Unicode icons with automatic ASCII fallbacks for terminals that dont support Unicode.

## Background

Modern terminals display beautiful Unicode symbols:
- Check marks (✓)
- Cross marks (✗)
- Arrows (→, ←, ↑, ↓)
- Bullets (•, ○, ◉)
- Status indicators (●, ◐, ○)

However, some terminals (especially older ones or certain CI environments) cant display these. We need fallbacks.

## Implementation

```rust
use crate::ui::context::OutputContext;

/// Icons with automatic fallback for non-Unicode terminals
pub struct Icons;

impl Icons {
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // STATUS INDICATORS
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Success indicator
    pub fn check(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "✓" } else { "[OK]" }
    }

    /// Failure indicator
    pub fn cross(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "✗" } else { "[FAIL]" }
    }

